# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# OnWay — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in every value before starting the server.
# Never commit .env or any real secret to version control.
#
# Generate random secrets with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000


# ── Security secrets ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED — both must be at least 64 random characters.
# Re-generate these for every new deployment; never reuse across projects.
JWT_SECRET=
SESSION_SECRET=


# ── Admin panel credentials ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED — credentials used to log in to the /admin dashboard.
ADMIN_USERNAME=
ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Emergency recovery password for /admin/reset-password.
# Set a strong random value. Leave empty to disable the endpoint entirely.
MASTER_RECOVERY_PASSWORD=


# ── Domain / CORS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED for production — comma-separated list of allowed origins.
# Must match the exact protocol + domain (+ port if non-standard) the app
# is served from.
# Examples:
#   https://api.example.com
#   https://api.example.com,https://app.example.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=

# Full URL of the backend API — baked into the mobile app bundle at build time.
# Must be set BEFORE running: npm run expo:static:build
# No trailing slash.
# Example: https://api.example.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=


# ── Firebase Admin SDK (Server-side) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED — paste the ENTIRE contents of the Firebase service account JSON
# as a single line (no line breaks).
#
# Download from:
#   Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service accounts
#   → Generate new private key → open the downloaded .json file
#   → copy all content and paste it here as one line.
#
# Example structure (all on one line):
#   {"type":"service_account","project_id":"...","private_key_id":"...","private_key":"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n","client_email":"...","client_id":"...","auth_uri":"...","token_uri":"..."}
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT=


# ── Firebase Client SDK (Mobile App / Realtime listeners) ─────────────────────
# REQUIRED — these values are baked into the mobile app bundle at build time.
# All keys must have the EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix so Expo exposes them to the JS bundle.
#
# Find values in:
#   Firebase Console → Project Settings → Your apps
#   → Web app → SDK setup and configuration → Config
#
# These are NOT secrets — Firebase client config is intentionally public and
# access is controlled by Firestore Security Rules, not by keeping keys hidden.
# They are placed in env vars so different environments (dev/staging/prod)
# can point to different Firebase projects without changing source code.
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=


# ── OTPIQ SMS Gateway ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED — API key from your otpiq.com dashboard.
OTP_IQ_API_KEY=

# Optional OTPIQ tuning (leave blank to use defaults):
OTP_IQ_BASE_URL=           # Default: https://api.otpiq.com/api
OTP_IQ_SENDER_ID=          # Approved sender ID from OTPIQ dashboard
OTP_IQ_PROVIDER=           # Channel: auto | sms | whatsapp | telegram  (default: auto)


# ── Google Maps ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED for map rendering in the mobile app.
# From: Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → API key
# Restrict the key to: Maps SDK for Android, Maps SDK for iOS
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=


# ── Google OAuth (Admin Panel — optional) ────────────────────────────────────
# Only required if using "Sign in with Google" for the admin panel.
# From: Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → OAuth 2.0 Client IDs
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# The Google account email that is allowed to access the admin panel.
ADMIN_GOOGLE_EMAIL=


# ── Development mode ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Controls the "0000" OTP test bypass. NEVER set to "true" in production.
# NODE_ENV=production disables this regardless of this flag.
DEV_MODE=false
